    "extras": [
      "Indians need a mainland China tourist visa; budget about ₹6,000–₹8,000 and keep hotel plus transport bookings handy for the application.",
      "Download and test your VPN before you land because Google, WhatsApp, Instagram and many western sites are blocked by the Great Firewall.",
      "WeChat and Alipay should be set up with an international Visa or Mastercard before departure; UPI is not accepted in China.",
      "Vegetarians should save temple restaurants and use the phrase 我是素食者 (I am vegetarian) when ordering.",
      "Avoid National Day Golden Week and Chinese New Year travel peaks; April–May and September–October are the easiest shoulder seasons.",
      "Book long-distance trains and Li River cruises 2–3 weeks ahead on Trip.com or 12306, especially for Beijing–Xi'an and Xi'an–Chengdu sectors."
